headlines.description: — Gordon Hayward scored 21 points, rookie center Mark Williams had a huge game with 18 points and 20 rebounds — both career highs — and the surging Charlotte Hornets defeated the Miami Heat 108-103 on Saturday night for their season-best fourth...
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams, Hornets send Heat to 4th straight defeat 108-103

headlines.description: — Myles Turner scored 24 points, Tyrese Haliburton had 15 points and 14 assists and the Indiana Pacers ran away from the Orlando Magic in the second half for a 121-108 victory on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner, Haliburton help Pacers rally past Magic 121-108

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 28 points to lead New York to a 128-106 rout of the New Orleans Pelicans on Saturday night as the Knicks celebrated the golden anniversary of their 1972-73 NBA championship team.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks rout Pelicans while honoring 1973 championship squad

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 23 points and seven rebounds as the Memphis Grizzlies raced to an early lead and coasted to a 112-94 victory over the Denver Nuggets on Saturday night in a matchup of the Western Conference’s top teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores 23, Grizzlies rout Nuggets in West showdown

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum buried the 3-pointer that put Boston ahead with 1.3 seconds left and casually backpedaled on defense before he turned to greet his teammates and — woosh! — a 70-foot shot sailed over his head and into the basket.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum's late 3 lifts Celtics past Embiid, 76ers 110-107

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 27 points and recent signee Kris Dunn added 15 as the Utah Jazz rallied from a 14-point deficit and beat the struggling San Antonio Spurs 118-102 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz rally late, send reeling Spurs to 16th straight loss
